doc.after: The Roman army succeeded in conquering many territories covering the entire Mediterranean region and coastal regions in southwestern Europe and north Africa These territories were home to many different cultural groups both urban populations and rural populations Generally speaking the eastern Mediterranean provinces were more urbanised than the western having previously been united under the Macedonian Empire and Hellenised by the influence of Greek culture 22
